By Henry Oladele Lagos – Commodore Ibrahim Shettima on Thursday formally took over as the commander, Nigerian Navy Ship (NNS) BEECROFT, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. He took over from Commodore Okon Eyo, who had been redeployed as the Director of Policy, Naval Headquarters. During his farewell remarks, Eyo charged officers and men to continue to be devoted to the country and the service as a whole. “I enjoin you never to rest on your oars, but to continue your devotion to the service and in particular extend the same cooperation or even better to the incoming commander,” he said. The outgone commander appreciated the Chief of Naval Staff , Vice Adm. Ibok-Ette Ibas, for giving him.the opportunity to serve as the BEECROFT Commander, adding that he would do his best in his new appointment.(NAN)